list.name: Default
list.comment: MVC refactoring - View no longer has any need to observe the Model as updating has been streamlined entirely through Controller class with update() method then updating the view appropriately, seem to still have bugs with races finishes as after one player has finished the other only gets one turn before vanishing

task.summary: Default task
quickfix on type issue when creating new state in Model
State rework
screenToModelCoord() method implemented for GameController to pass accurate MouseEvent coordinates back to Model in the future
added local LineSprite class
added global colour constants and fillremainder feature for mass loading tiles of one type
added drawing next possible move circle selectors
added custom Observer and Observable interfaces back in for change-propagation between MVC elements (might remove later if JavaFX Properties are deemed a more appropriate solution)
various MVC updates
quickfix for null return value in Racetrack.getStartPosition()
added strip read functionality for loading groups of the same tile in one file line
model observers nullpointerexception fixed
fixed null return on Model.getCurrentState() (possibly one of the daftest errors I have ever unwittingly subjected myself to - NOTE: CHECK ALL RETURN STATEMENTS ON GETTERS IN FUTURE)
model work on checking valid moves
fixed racers not drawing bug
added AI package and BFS DFS classes
refactored getPossibleNextPoints heavy lifting from Player into Racer
fixed concurrentmodificationexception in RacetrackPane
fixed row and col inverted Point parameters passed in model.gridPointInput()
racer movement now working almost as expected (hallelujah)
racer trail drawing work in progress

need to work on trail drawing logic, probably due a complete rewrite, without the copying from stack to stack then to arraylist, too convoluted and makes it totally unreadable for debugging this issue
debugging trail drawing, still not found a solution
trails working
some API javadoc commentary
wall collision detection and racer resetting with velocity killing
added some straight line maths functions to Vect
Terrain between points detection work
more Terrain between points detection work, most of the logic is in place but currently still broken, need to do a dry run through the whole method and helper methods from Vect

rename FinishTile to CheckpointTile and introduced zone numbering system, tiles with the same zone number will be part of the same checkpoint area, zone numbers start at 0 and increment, zone numbers with the highest value represent the final checkpoint (finish line)
terrain between 2 points algorithm complete with basic testing, need thorough tests on wide case range
added minimonza racetrack layout
refactored Terrain to remove slide and chaos - slide is now negative resistance and chaos has been removed from the game

fixed issues with equals and hashcode methods in Tile that were causing issues when removing tiles from the racetrack to overwrite with checkpoints, pretty much at v1.0.0 now, just need to put in checks for all players finishing the race, then final testing/debugging, then can start on styling and AI for v1.1.0
fixed issue regarding next move mouseclick detection being slightly off and detecting in the wrong circle occasionally

implemented mechanism for checking when game is over i.e. all players have crossed the last checkpoint in a legal fashion, needs debugged, seem to be getting an infinite recursion problem, likely due to my skip player method in State
partially fixed game over infinite recursion bug
racetrack files bump

added *.vrff extension filter for file selection, refactored resources into separate folder and added mechanism for automatically loading resources into vector files directory in user's home directory
final zone end i.e. zone 0 start (finish line) now draws as black
tidied up some print statements
